Speech Emotion Recognition (SER) Bot

An interactive Deep Learning web application powered by a **1D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)** and **TensorFlow** to classify emotions from speech signals in real-time.

Live Deployment URL: https://speech-emotion-ser.streamlit.app

Features
* Live Audio Recording: Record voice samples live via your microphone container or upload `.wav`, `.mp3`, or `.m4a` file tracks.
* Feature Extraction Tracking: Extracts a stacked 180-dimensional feature vector (40 MFCCs, 12 Chroma, and 128 Mel Spectrogram dimensions) averaged over the time axis.
* Real-Time Visualization: Interactive time-domain waveform visualization powered by Plotly.
* Deep Evaluation: Complete probability distribution breakdown across 8 core target emotion nodes.

Tech Stack
* Framework: Streamlit
* Deep Learning Engine: TensorFlow / Keras
* Signal Processing: Librosa & Soundfile
* Data Visualization: Plotly & Matplotlib

How to Run Locally
If you are on Windows, you can launch the app locally without manual setup:
1. Clone or download this repository.
2. Simply double-click the `run_app.bat` file. 

* The bootloader script will automatically detect or create your local virtual Python environment, fetch all missing dependencies from `requirements.txt`, and boot up the web interface on your localhost.
